notes: 12th Men: R Telemachus (South Africa) and GD McGrath (Australia)
Klusener reached 3,000 ODI runs when he scored his 14th run
Klusener became the fastest player to reach the double of 3,000 runs and 150 wickets in 131 mins (previous record: Imran Khan in 143 matches)
Rhodes (when he scored his 80th run) passed WJ Cronje's record as highest South African run scored against Australia (1364 runs)
Gilchrist reached 4,000 ODI runs when he scored his 11th run (9th Australian to pass 4,000 ODI runs)
Martyn reached 2,000 ODI runs when he scored his 29th run (13th Australian to pass 2,000 ODI runs)

stories.title: Australian last-wicket pair snatch tie in Potchefstroom
stories.summary: Australia's last wicket pair of Jimmy Maher and Nathan Hauritz snatched a remarkable tie in the third Standard Bank One-Day International in Potchefstroom on Wednesday after South Africa seemed set to take their first victory of the series
